evidence.source_document: First Amended Complaint for Declaratory and Injunctive Relief
evidence.text: Plaintiffs seek a temporary restraining order and preliminary and permanent injunction enjoining Sections 2(a), (b), (d), (f), (g), and (h) of Executive Order 14193, as amended, Sections 2, 3(a), (b), (c), (d), (e), and (f), Section 4(a), (b), (c), and (d), of Executive Order 14257, as amended, and Section 14 of Proclamations 10896 and 10895.

IT IS ORDERED that Defendants’ Motion to Transfer to the United States Court of International Trade (Doc. 18) is GRANTED. This case shall be transferred to the United States Court of International Trade pursuant to 28 U.S.C. § 1631.
